      • isAvailable

        public javax.ws.rs.core.Response isAvailable()
        Checks if a Node is currently available. Availability of a node means that every port of this node is not affiliated with a PVID/Native VLan ID. If only one port has a PVID on the NetComponent then the whole node is not available for use. Possible HTTP status codes:
      • 200: The Node is free to use
      • 403: The Node is currently used by another user. The Node ID and the User are described in the message body, if the user can be determined.
      • 500: The Controller could not retrieve the requested information a specified error description is located in the message body
Returns:
Returns an outbound Response Object with status code and message body
